The paper deals with algorithms and heuristics for metric properties of graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on analyzing the performances of these algorithms and proving their efficiency on certain classes of graphs suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of probabilistic models to generate power law random graphs suggests that it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the mention of central vertices and distance oracles suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
